  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="SV">ADB -  Output-Based Aid (OBA) in Clean Energy Financing Partnership Facility</narrative>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">ADB - Output-Based Aid (OBA) in Clean Energy Financing Partnership Facility</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Output based aid component to the Clean Energy Fund in ADB.</narrative>
   <narrative xml:lang="SV">Output based aid komponent till Clean Energy Fund i ADB.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Output-based Aid (OBA) is an instrument for Clean Energy Financing Partnership Facility (CEFPF), referring to contribution ID 51020107, aims to promote access to electricity for the poor, and mainly contributing to the achievement of the access to energy output within the CEFPF&apos;s results framework (Output 4 - Expected Access to Energy Benefits).
The OBA is an approach designed to increase access to and the delivery of basic services to the poor using performance-based subsidies. OBA links the payment of a subsidy to the delivery of specific services or &#x201C;outputs&#x201D;. The service delivery is contracted out to a third party, the service provider who is responsible for providing the up-front financing of the contracted services until the agreed upon outputs are delivered and independently verified. The subsidy is explicitly targeted at the poor, depending on the context and the environment.</narrative>
  </description>
